race.comment: The biggest field of the day and one of the more open races to finish. ENUFF SEDUCTION (1) might be the one. He's a winner first-up and draws well to get the perfect run here. He's run well in better races. LET'S TROT (15) is a Victorian visitor now back in the care of Reece Goodwin. A recent jump out win suggests that he might be able to get back to some of his better form here. DAPPER DON (16) has only won a maiden but he's been placed six times. He will roll forward with no weight on his back and might take some catching. KALASEC (3) mixes his form but warrants respect in this grade, while ZATANNA (13) is another who can make her own luck on speed and run a cheeky race.
